      "module_path": "tddd::catalogue_document_codec",
      "docs": "Infrastructure codec for CatalogueDocument JSON serialization / deserialization. Stateless unit struct; decode, load, encode are all associated functions (no self receiver). Modify from baseline: handles the new data-carrying DataRole (15 variants with struct/unit payloads) and ContractRole (4 variants, Repository with aggregate field). NonEmptyVec<TypeRef> codec for EventPolicy.reacts_to — empty JSON array is a decode error. decode() takes (json: &str, filename_stem: &str) — filename_stem is the file name part before '-types.json', used for crate_name validation. load() takes &Path (borrows, does not consume). All payload fields (identity, invariants, exclusive_members, shared_value_objects, emits, handles, reacts_to, aggregate) managed here with appropriate serde default / skip_serializing_if annotations.",
